events.description: The city of Tyre falls to the Venetian Crusade after a siege of nineteen weeks.
events.html: • 1124 – The city of Tyre falls to the Venetian Crusade after a siege of nineteen weeks.

events.description: A retrial verdict acquits Joan of Arc of heresy 25 years after her execution.
events.html: • 1456 – A retrial verdict acquits Joan of Arc of heresy 25 years after her execution.

events.description: Spanish conquistadores defeat a larger Aztec army at the Battle of Otumba.
events.html: • 1520 – Spanish conquistadores defeat a larger Aztec army at the Battle of Otumba.

events.description: Jacques Cartier makes his first contact with aboriginal peoples in what is now Canada.
events.html: • 1534 – Jacques Cartier makes his first contact with aboriginal peoples in what is now Canada.

events.description: The Raid of the Redeswire is the last major battle between England and Scotland.
events.html: • 1575 – The Raid of the Redeswire is the last major battle between England and Scotland.

events.description: The Treaty of Nemours abolishes tolerance to Protestants in France.
events.html: • 1585 – The Treaty of Nemours abolishes tolerance to Protestants in France.

events.description: An English fleet completes the destruction of a French merchant fleet off Fort St Pierre, Martinique during the Second Anglo-Dutch War.
events.html: • 1667 – An English fleet completes the destruction of a French merchant fleet off Fort St Pierre, Martinique during the Second Anglo-Dutch War.[1]

events.description: The Battle of Larga between the Russian Empire and the Ottoman Empire takes place.
events.html: • 1770 – The Battle of Larga between the Russian Empire and the Ottoman Empire takes place.

events.description: American forces retreating from Fort Ticonderoga are defeated in the Battle of Hubbardton.
events.html: • 1777 – American forces retreating from Fort Ticonderoga are defeated in the Battle of Hubbardton.

events.description: As a result of the XYZ Affair, the US Congress rescinds the Treaty of Alliance with France sparking the "Quasi-War".
events.html: • 1798 – As a result of the XYZ Affair, the US Congress rescinds the Treaty of Alliance with France sparking the "Quasi-War".

events.description: The first Treaty of Tilsit between France and Russia is signed, ending hostilities between the two countries in the War of the Fourth Coalition.
events.html: • 1807 – The first Treaty of Tilsit between France and Russia is signed, ending hostilities between the two countries in the War of the Fourth Coalition.

events.description: In New York City, four nights of rioting against abolitionists began.
events.html: • 1834 – In New York City, four nights of rioting against abolitionists began.

events.description: US troops occupy Monterey and Yerba Buena, thus beginning the US conquest of California.
events.html: • 1846 – US troops occupy Monterey and Yerba Buena, thus beginning the US conquest of California.

events.description: The United States begins its first military draft; exemptions cost $300.
events.html: • 1863 – The United States begins its first military draft; exemptions cost $300.

events.description: Four conspirators in the assassination of Abraham Lincoln are hanged.
events.html: • 1865 – Four conspirators in the assassination of Abraham Lincoln are hanged.

events.description: The Katipunan is established, the discovery of which by Spanish authorities initiated the Philippine Revolution.
events.html: • 1892 – The Katipunan is established, the discovery of which by Spanish authorities initiated the Philippine Revolution.

events.description: US President William McKinley signs the Newlands Resolution annexing Hawaii as a territory of the United States.
events.html: • 1898 – US President William McKinley signs the Newlands Resolution annexing Hawaii as a territory of the United States.

events.description: Florenz Ziegfeld Jr. staged his first Follies on the roof of the New York Theater in New York City.
events.html: • 1907 – Florenz Ziegfeld Jr. staged his first Follies on the roof of the New York Theater in New York City.

events.description: The United States, UK, Japan, and Russia sign the North Pacific Fur Seal Convention of 1911 banning open-water seal hunting, the first international treaty to address wildlife preservation issues.
events.html: • 1911 – The United States, UK, Japan, and Russia sign the North Pacific Fur Seal Convention of 1911 banning open-water seal hunting, the first international treaty to address wildlife preservation issues.

entities.name: North Pacific Fur Seal Convention of 1911

events.description: The First Battle of the Isonzo comes to an end.
events.html: • 1915 – The First Battle of the Isonzo comes to an end.

events.description: Colombo Town Guard officer Henry Pedris is executed in British Ceylon for allegedly inciting persecution of Muslims.
events.html: • 1915 – Colombo Town Guard officer Henry Pedris is executed in British Ceylon for allegedly inciting persecution of Muslims.

events.description: The New Zealand Labour Party was founded in Wellington.
events.html: • 1916 – The New Zealand Labour Party was founded in Wellington.

events.description: Sliced bread is sold for the first time (on the inventor's 48th birthday) by the Chillicothe Baking Company of Chillicothe, Missouri.
events.html: • 1928 – Sliced bread is sold for the first time (on the inventor's 48th birthday) by the Chillicothe Baking Company of Chillicothe, Missouri.

events.description: Industrialist Henry J. Kaiser begins construction of Boulder Dam (now known as Hoover Dam).
events.html: • 1930 – Industrialist Henry J. Kaiser begins construction of Boulder Dam (now known as Hoover Dam).

events.description: The Finnish far-right Lapua Movement organises the Peasant March demonstration in Helsinki to put pressure on the government to prohibit communist activities.
events.html: • 1930 – The Finnish far-right Lapua Movement organises the Peasant March demonstration in Helsinki to put pressure on the government to prohibit communist activities.[2]

events.description: The Marco Polo Bridge Incident (Lugou Bridge) provides the Imperial Japanese Army with a pretext for starting the Second Sino-Japanese War (China-Japan War).
events.html: • 1937 – The Marco Polo Bridge Incident (Lugou Bridge) provides the Imperial Japanese Army with a pretext for starting the Second Sino-Japanese War (China-Japan War).

events.description: The Peel Commission Report recommends the partition of Palestine, which was the first formal recommendation for partition in the history of Palestine.
events.html: • 1937 – The Peel Commission Report recommends the partition of Palestine, which was the first formal recommendation for partition in the history of Palestine.

events.description: The US occupation of Iceland replaces the UK's occupation.
events.html: • 1941 – The US occupation of Iceland replaces the UK's occupation.

events.description: World War II: Largest Banzai charge of the Pacific War at the Battle of Saipan.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: Largest Banzai charge of the Pacific War at the Battle of Saipan.

events.description: Mother Francesca S. Cabrini becomes the first American to be canonized.
events.html: • 1946 – Mother Francesca S. Cabrini becomes the first American to be canonized.

events.description: Howard Hughes nearly dies when his XF-11 reconnaissance aircraft prototype crashes in a Beverly Hills neighborhood.
events.html: • 1946 – Howard Hughes nearly dies when his XF-11 reconnaissance aircraft prototype crashes in a Beverly Hills neighborhood.

events.description: The ocean liner SS United States passes Bishop Rock on her maiden voyage, breaking the transatlantic speed record to become the fastest passenger ship in the world.
events.html: • 1952 – The ocean liner SS United States passes Bishop Rock on her maiden voyage, breaking the transatlantic speed record to become the fastest passenger ship in the world.

events.description: Ernesto "Che" Guevara sets out on a trip through Bolivia, Peru, Ecuador, Panama, Costa Rica, Nicaragua, Honduras, and El Salvador.
events.html: • 1953 – Ernesto "Che" Guevara sets out on a trip through Bolivia, Peru, Ecuador, Panama, Costa Rica, Nicaragua, Honduras, and El Salvador.

events.description: US President Dwight D. Eisenhower signs the Alaska Statehood Act into law.
events.html: • 1958 – US President Dwight D. Eisenhower signs the Alaska Statehood Act into law.

events.description: Venus occults the star Regulus. This rare event is used to determine the diameter of Venus and the structure of the Venusian atmosphere.
events.html: • 1959 – Venus occults the star Regulus. This rare event is used to determine the diameter of Venus and the structure of the Venusian atmosphere.

events.description: Alitalia Flight 771 crashes in Junnar, Maharashtra, India, killing 94 people.
events.html: • 1962 – Alitalia Flight 771 crashes in Junnar, Maharashtra, India, killing 94 people.[3]

events.description: Buddhist crisis: Police commanded by Ngô Đình Nhu, brother and chief political adviser of South Vietnam President Ngo Dinh Diem, attacked a group of American journalists who were covering a protest.
events.html: • 1963 – Buddhist crisis: Police commanded by Ngô Đình Nhu, brother and chief political adviser of South Vietnam President Ngo Dinh Diem, attacked a group of American journalists who were covering a protest.

events.description: The Solomon Islands becomes independent from the United Kingdom.
events.html: • 1978 – The Solomon Islands becomes independent from the United Kingdom.

events.description: Institution of sharia law in Iran.
events.html: • 1980 – Institution of sharia law in Iran.

events.description: During the Lebanese Civil War, 83 Tiger militants are killed during what will be known as the Safra massacre.
events.html: • 1980 – During the Lebanese Civil War, 83 Tiger militants are killed during what will be known as the Safra massacre.

events.description: US President Ronald Reagan nominates Sandra Day O'Connor to become the first female member of the Supreme Court of the United States.
events.html: • 1981 – US President Ronald Reagan nominates Sandra Day O'Connor to become the first female member of the Supreme Court of the United States.

entities.name: Supreme Court of the United States

events.description: Cold War: Samantha Smith, a US schoolgirl, flies to the Soviet Union at the invitation of Secretary General Yuri Andropov.

entities.name: List of leaders of the Soviet Union

events.description: Boris Becker becomes the youngest male player ever to win Wimbledon at age 17.
events.html: • 1985 – Boris Becker becomes the youngest male player ever to win Wimbledon at age 17.

events.description: Yugoslav Wars: The Brioni Agreement ends the ten-day independence war in Slovenia against the rest of the Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia.
events.html: • 1991 – Yugoslav Wars: The Brioni Agreement ends the ten-day independence war in Slovenia against the rest of the Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia.

events.description: The New York Court of Appeals rules that women have the same right as men to go topless in public.
events.html: • 1992 – The New York Court of Appeals rules that women have the same right as men to go topless in public.

events.description: The Turkish Armed Forces withdraw from northern Iraq after assisting the Kurdistan Democratic Party in the Iraqi Kurdish Civil War.
events.html: • 1997 – The Turkish Armed Forces withdraw from northern Iraq after assisting the Kurdistan Democratic Party in the Iraqi Kurdish Civil War.

events.description: NASA Opportunity rover, MER-B or Mars Exploration Rover–B, was launched into space aboard a Delta II rocket.
events.html: • 2003 – NASA Opportunity rover, MER-B or Mars Exploration Rover–B, was launched into space aboard a Delta II rocket.

events.description: A series of four explosions occurs on London's transport system, killing 56 people, including four suicide bombers, and injuring over 700 others.
events.html: • 2005 – A series of four explosions occurs on London's transport system, killing 56 people, including four suicide bombers, and injuring over 700 others.

events.description: The first Live Earth benefit concert was held in 11 locations around the world.
events.html: • 2007 – The first Live Earth benefit concert was held in 11 locations around the world.

events.description: At least 172 people are killed in a flash flood in the Krasnodar Krai region of Russia.
events.html: • 2012 – At least 172 people are killed in a flash flood in the Krasnodar Krai region of Russia.

events.description: A De Havilland Otter air taxi crashes in Soldotna, Alaska, killing ten people.
events.html: • 2013 – A De Havilland Otter air taxi crashes in Soldotna, Alaska, killing ten people.

events.description: Ex-US Army soldier Micah Xavier Johnson shoots fourteen policemen during an anti-police protest in downtown Dallas, Texas, killing five of them. He is subsequently killed by a robot-delivered bomb.
events.html: • 2016 – Ex-US Army soldier Micah Xavier Johnson shoots fourteen policemen during an anti-police protest in downtown Dallas, Texas, killing five of them. He is subsequently killed by a robot-delivered bomb.
